 been an opening ceremony quite like it.\", \"from\": 363, \"to\": 506, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all partners https://doi.org/10.64628/AA.hn9yrvr6e Share article Print article\", \"from\": 368, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"an opening ceremony\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the first time in Olympic Games history, the ceremony took place outside a stadium arena.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 601, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Games history\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 551}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 565}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 576}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium arena\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 600}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a rainy and miserable Paris evening, enormous crowds - most who paid no fee to attend - lined the banks of the Seine to witness this outdoor promenade of history, art and sport as 100 boats carrying 10,500 athletes sailed down the river.\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 632, \"end\": 637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3082590092488224e-25, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4557045813638896e-26, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"enormous crowds\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 662}, {\"ngram\": \"no fee\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 685}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 713}, {\"ngram\": \"this outdoor promenade\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 760}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 776}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 786}, {\"ngram\": \"100 boats\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 799}, {\"ngram\": \"10,500 athletes\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 824}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Designed to showcase the depth of French culture and celebrate the Olympics as a source of human greatness and unity, the ceremony combined the traditional and the irreverent.\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the depth\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 924}, {\"ngram\": \"a source\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 936}, {\"ngram\": \"human greatness\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 955}, {\"ngram\": \"unity\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 979}, {\"ngram\": \"the irreverent\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1023}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris featured as the unmistakable backdrop.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3082590092488224e-25, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the unmistakable backdrop\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony marked the first since 2018 that has not had to work around COVID restrictions.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1163, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ceremony\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1083}, {\"ngram\": \"restrictions\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1162}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the world watched, it took place amid a global context of war, invasion and genocide.\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1199}, {\"ngram\": \"a global context\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1221}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1228}, {\"ngram\": \"invasion\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"genocide\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1251}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Within the performances and speeches featured in the ceremony, there were aspects designed to address and acknowledge this, and promote peace and inclusion.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the performances\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"speeches\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1314}, {\"ngram\": \"aspects\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1334}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1394}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1408}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony was divided into thematic chapters, includingFraternit\\u00e9(fraternity),Sororit\\u00e9(sorority),Sportive(sportsmanship),Solidarit\\u00e9(solidarity),Solennit\\u00e9(solemnity) and\\u00c9ternit\\u00e9(eternity).\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1601, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ceremony\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1423}, {\"ngram\": \"thematic chapters\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"includingFraternit\\u00e9(fraternity),Sororit\\u00e9(sorority),Sportive(sportsmanship),Solidarit\\u00e9(solidarity),Solennit\\u00e9(solemnity\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These were used as prompts to underpin each section of the sprawling, epic ceremony.\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"prompts\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1628}, {\"ngram\": \"each section\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1653}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprawling, epic ceremony\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1685}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Across the three hours, we travelled throughout Paris.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1736, \"end\": 1741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3082590092488224e-25, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the three hours\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1710}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Artists and sportspeople from across the broad spectrum of each of these fields were featured and celebrated.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1852, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Artists\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1750}, {\"ngram\": \"sportspeople\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1767}, {\"ngram\": \"the broad spectrum\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1798}, {\"ngram\": \"these fields\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1822}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All was underpinned by an amazing soundtrack featuring French electro-pop bangers, classical music and opera.\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1909, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9997332882689223, \"rank\": 0.00023190412084259264, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an amazing soundtrack\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1898}, {\"ngram\": \"classical music\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 1952}, {\"ngram\": \"opera\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1962}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony was anchored by a masked torch bearer who initially arrived at the Olympic stadium only to realise they were in the wrong place.\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 2106, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phras